import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['daily_return'] = data.groupby('symbol')['close'].pct_change()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    for symbol in data['symbol'].unique():
        ax.hist(data[data['symbol'] == symbol]['daily_return'], bins=50, alpha=0.5, label=symbol)
    ax.axvline(data['daily_return'].mean(), color='k', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='mean')
    ax.axvline(data['daily_return'].median(), color='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='median')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily returns for each stock?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    stocks = data.columns
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(len(stocks), len(stocks), figsize=(20,20))
    fig.suptitle('What is the correlation between the daily returns of each stock?')
    for i in range(len(stocks)):
        for j in range(len(stocks)):
            axs[i,j].scatter(data[stocks[i]], data[stocks[j]])
            axs[i,j].set_xlabel(stocks[i])
            axs[i,j].set_ylabel(stocks[j])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    avg_vol = data.groupby('Name')['Volume'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_vol.index, avg_vol.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Stock Name')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Daily Volume')
    ax.axhline(avg_vol.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {avg_vol.mean():,.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    stocks = data.pivot(index='date', columns='stock', values='close')
    stocks.plot(figsize=(10,6))
    plt.title('What is the trend of closing prices for each stock over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Closing Price')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['PE Ratio'] = data['Price']/data['Earnings/Share']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data.groupby('Stock')['PE Ratio'].mean(), bins=20, alpha=0.5, label='Mean P/E Ratio')
    ax.hist(data.groupby('Stock')['PE Ratio'].median(), bins=20, alpha=0.5, label='Median P/E Ratio')
    ax.axvline(data['PE Ratio'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean P/E Ratio: {data["PE Ratio"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['PE Ratio'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median P/E Ratio: {data["PE Ratio"].median():.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('P/E Ratio')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
